<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I didn't order the Limited edition V8 mustang to be told on delivery day that:<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh we didn't have enough spark plugs so there's only 5 in the engine.... we will install the other 3 on a later maintenance service. (aka patch day)&quot; --- yet it never happens<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes we know you have power windows and door locks but the switches for those items will have to be put in on a later maintenance service. (aka patch day)&quot; --- yet it never happens<br>
<br>
Then one fine day you ask when your going to get the plugs and switches in your car so you can use it to it's purchased potential and they say to you.<br>
&quot;Well for us to put those in it will be <br>
3 plugs $25<br>
door switches $50<br>
window s/w $75<br>
Labor $435<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The point that a lot of people are upset about is that certain things were promised in this game from the jump. It's wrong for Sony/VI to now get around to offering those same things only to those willing to pay more money than what was originally agreed upon.  Sure you should expect to pay more for new things, but not for what you should have had from the first time you installed the game.<br>
